tg2sip-webrtc (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rename the config file, everywhere it's read or shipped, from the
    original settings.ini/config.ini naming to tg2sip.conf - .ini reads as
    a Windows-ism, .conf matches normal Debian daemon convention (see e.g.
    nginx.conf, apache2.conf for the same directory/filename pattern):
    - The installed system config is now /etc/tg2sip-webrtc/tg2sip.conf
      (was /etc/tg2sip-webrtc/config.ini).
    - The tracked source template is now tg2sip.conf at the repo root
      (was settings.ini), and the build-generated, never-clobbered-in-
      place copy CMake drops next to the binary is now
      tg2sip.conf.sample (was config.ini.sample).
    - The dev/in-tree cwd fallback resolve_config_path() falls back to is
      now tg2sip.conf (was settings.ini).
    Updated every doc/packaging reference accordingly (README,
    postinst/postrm, the systemd unit, both man pages).

 -- Vlad Vorobyev <vlad.vorobev@gmail.com>  Thu, 16 Jul 2026 11:56:09 +0300

tg2sip-webrtc (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging. Builds PJSIP 2.9 and TDLib (master) from
    source into a private prefix at package-build time (neither is
    packaged in Debian); both link statically, so the resulting
    tg2sip-webrtc/gen_db binaries carry no runtime dependency on them.
    Ships a systemd service (tg2sip-webrtc.service), a dedicated system
    user, and a config template at /etc/tg2sip-webrtc/config.ini.

 -- Vlad Vorobyev <vlad.vorobev@gmail.com>  Wed, 15 Jul 2026 16:07:21 +0300
